   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">No surprise to see what direction Clinton is going</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55612543#c2?mode=alone;showrate=1#c2">32+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:279088">doroma</a>, <a href="/user/uid:99179">bnasley</a>, <a href="/user/uid:74622">DiesIrae</a>, <a href="/user/uid:311479">Stude Dude</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17553">Heart of the Rockies</a>, <a href="/user/uid:28795">wader</a>, <a href="/user/uid:30523">psnyder</a>, <a href="/user/uid:78008">rage</a>, <a href="/user/uid:49600">Lying eyes</a>, <a href="/user/uid:159850">p gorden lippy</a>, <a href="/user/uid:260470">RockyMtnHigh</a>, <a href="/user/uid:35014">NYFM</a>, <a href="/user/uid:333891">Smoh</a>, <a href="/user/uid:25604">wishingwell</a>, <a href="/user/uid:180156">Matthew D Jones</a>, <a href="/user/uid:115624">Thomas Twinnings</a>, <a href="/user/uid:327009">goodpractice</a>, <a href="/user/uid:61752">Rogneid</a>, <a href="/user/uid:61869">Hannibal</a>, <a href="/user/uid:2823">Chi</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:175854">Onomastic</a>, <a href="/user/uid:321118">Linda1961</a>, <a href="/user/uid:96369">Matt Z</a>, <a href="/user/uid:15394">frisco</a>, <a href="/user/uid:996524">elenacarlena</a>, <a href="/user/uid:643561">eagleray</a>, <a href="/user/uid:3037">Phoenix Woman</a>, <a href="/user/uid:6264">Geenius at Wrok</a>, <a href="/user/uid:129947">Mad Season</a>, <a href="/user/uid:192385">marleycat</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17036">Creosote</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>But, I thought this was interesting, coming from Jeb Bush:<br /></p>
<blockquote>“Something is holding them back," he continued. "Not a lack of ambition. Not a lack of hope. Not because they’re lazy, or see themselves as victims. Something else. Something is an artificial weight on their shoulders. ...</blockquote>
Does he ever answer what that "something else" is?
<p>If its government regulations as Jack Kelly says, or if Bush uses that rhetoric to rationalize how business needs to be taxed less and regulated less, I think thats going to fall flat.</p>

