  <div class="ct">
  
<p>They just need to neutralize income inequality as a political issue for 2016. &nbsp;It's the strongest card in the Democratic hand, so if Republicans take it away, they've got a much better chance to win. &nbsp;Much easier for them to do that if Clinton tosses it away herself.</p>
<p>If we have a Republican candidate flapping his gums meaninglessly about income inequality, and a Democratic candidate flapping her gums meaninglessly about it, what's going to happen? &nbsp;No outflanking needed, just the same show of rhetorical concern masking the same oligarchic economic policies on both sides, give or take a couple of tossed bones.</p>
<p>I'm really encouraged that Democrats are once more going to try to win an election by blurring the distinctions between them and their opponents. &nbsp;Because that's always worked so well....</p>

