  <a href="/user/uid:31366">Dallasdoc</a>, <a href="/user/uid:6493">dfarrah</a>, <a href="/user/uid:171754">tapu dali</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146659">notrouble</a>, <a href="/user/uid:947717">travelerxxx</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1303">cslewis</a>, <a href="/user/uid:996524">elenacarlena</a>, <a href="/user/uid:52984">snacksandpop</a>, <a href="/user/uid:19716">TracieLynn</a>, <a href="/user/uid:198415">CarolinNJ</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75329">JVolvo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:125975">Metro99</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17036">Creosote</a>, <a href="/user/uid:987053">montanaguy</a>, <a href="/user/uid:139379">J M F</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>I think they recognize it, not as an opportunity, though, but as a threat to their neoliberal consensus. In neoliberalism they thought that they had found the way to marry distributional concerns and fiscal conservatism that would enable them to finesse the political problems posed by both. They were wrong, but they don't yet accept that.</p>
<p>I am not looking forward to 2016, and I am not at all sure that it will once again find me knocking on doors for the Democratic presidential candidate.</p>

