<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55615400#c178?mode=alone;showrate=1#c178">26+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:70454">KenBee</a>, <a href="/user/uid:89027">wa ma</a>, <a href="/user/uid:31366">Dallasdoc</a>, <a href="/user/uid:160026">flitedocnm</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1303">cslewis</a>, <a href="/user/uid:996524">elenacarlena</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146420">maryabein</a>, <a href="/user/uid:327681">SixSixSix</a>, <a href="/user/uid:6264">Geenius at Wrok</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1800">Emmet</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75329">JVolvo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:140907">aufklaerer</a>, <a href="/user/uid:220861">wolf advocate</a>, <a href="/user/uid:3419">Alexa</a>, <a href="/user/uid:630">claude</a>, <a href="/user/uid:125975">Metro99</a>, <a href="/user/uid:57841">ivorybill</a>, <a href="/user/uid:103993">jhop7</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17036">Creosote</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75534">NearlyNormal</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:111992">flowerfarmer</a>, <a href="/user/uid:143254">BoiseBlue</a>, <a href="/user/uid:139379">J M F</a>, <a href="/user/uid:66934">Pacifist</a>, <a href="/user/uid:62874">mightymouse</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>so afraid of being angry? &nbsp;There are so many reasons that that resonates with Americans right now - legitimate reasons, I might add.</p>
<p>And if people on the Democratic side are going to continue to make the case that women and people of color cannot channel anger when it is totally legitimate, then you can kiss the prospects for women and people of color to hold high office goodbye.</p>
<p>I remember what happened to Geradine Ferraro. &nbsp;That fiasco set women in this country back decades AND, dammit (I am angry about this especially) protected the exclusive domain that had been preserved for white males for decades longer than it should ever have happened.</p>
<p>The exposure that Warren has received has help both her and her cause because people have taken to the <i>content</i> of her commentary; and I would argue that her passionate delivery has helped her image, not hurt.</p>
<p>Monotone technocrats just are not inspiring.</p>
<p>Anyway, as a woman, if you tell me that I can't express legitimate anger over a real problem <b>because I am a woman</b>, then I'm going to tell you to fuck off. &nbsp;I've been there in my professional world where some fucktard makes the case that a woman can't express legitimate anger as a way to shut down <i>legitimate</i> criticism, challenge or other attempts by a woman to push for solutions to problems.</p>
<p>Every woman who might read this comment will know exactly what I am talking about. &nbsp;A man freaks out and people think he's "strong" and a woman gets angry and people try to paint her as a "bitch" - or talk about whether or not she's getting enough sex or has her period. &nbsp;It is a bunch of fucking bullshit and I refuse to participate in continuing this oppressive ruse by promoting the idea that women in politics need to watch what they say and how they say it because they are women.</p>
<p>People who don't like the idea of a woman for President won't like it no matter how much that woman attempts to kiss their ass.</p>
<p>Sorry, but you hit a HUGE nerve for me. &nbsp;I run large crews of people in a male dominated industry and I haven't managed to get where I have by letting assholes run over me by playing the "you're bitchy" card. &nbsp;I am not a bitch. &nbsp;I am extremely fair and when I see something wrong, I want it fixed. &nbsp;People who don't want to fix things, get gone meanwhile I get results and my trusted crew who do take pride in their work continue to work with me because they know I'm looking out for all of us and trying to do a good job. &nbsp;I give them all the credit for being awesome and caring about the work product we create together.</p>

  </div>
