<li id="c130">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55614702">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">"We Suck Less" doesn't work anymore</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55614702#c130?mode=alone;showrate=1#c130">32+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:18605">opinionated</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:37824">inclusiveheart</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146659">notrouble</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100108">jello5929</a>, <a href="/user/uid:947717">travelerxxx</a>, <a href="/user/uid:70454">KenBee</a>, <a href="/user/uid:62669">tallen387</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1470">chuck utzman</a>, <a href="/user/uid:107208">Keith930</a>, <a href="/user/uid:39858">Hillbilly Dem</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1303">cslewis</a>, <a href="/user/uid:231799">Punditus Maximus</a>, <a href="/user/uid:996524">elenacarlena</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146420">maryabein</a>, <a href="/user/uid:199851">TRPChicago</a>, <a href="/user/uid:46465">NoMoreLies</a>, <a href="/user/uid:976165">Pablo Bocanegra</a>, <a href="/user/uid:327681">SixSixSix</a>, <a href="/user/uid:6264">Geenius at Wrok</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100167">Midwesterners</a>, <a href="/user/uid:198415">CarolinNJ</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75329">JVolvo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:630">claude</a>, <a href="/user/uid:125975">Metro99</a>, <a href="/user/uid:89890">blue armadillo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:103993">jhop7</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17036">Creosote</a>, <a href="/user/uid:987053">montanaguy</a>, <a href="/user/uid:111992">flowerfarmer</a>, <a href="/user/uid:139379">J M F</a>, <a href="/user/uid:62874">mightymouse</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>In order to start winning elections again, Democrats have to begin to <b>actually suck less.</b> &nbsp;When it comes to issues of income inequality, they're not quite hitting that mark. Yes, Republicans want to make things worse, but Democrats haven't done anything to discernibly make things better for most people.</p>
<p>Telling voters that our phony schemes will help you, whereas their phony schemes won't, is a strategy Democrats have been trying for a while now. &nbsp;Voters aren't buying it, perhaps you've noticed. &nbsp;The time for Democrats to try telling the truth and advocating something meaningful for the large majority of voters is at hand.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig">
Our form of democracy is bribery, on the highest scale. --Gore Vidal
</p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:31366">Dallasdoc</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55614702#c130">Sun Feb 08, 2015 at 02:44:15 PM PST</a></p>
