<li id="c337">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55620834">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">They have to focus on labor, but they</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55620834#c337?mode=alone;showrate=1#c337">1+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:57841">ivorybill</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>have to stop targeting their messaging towards discrete factions of labor.</p>
<p>First of all, it is now "that bad" and pretty much everyone who lives in this country in say the greater portion of 75% of the lower rungs are currently living with some sort of anxiety based on a feeling of economic insecurity. &nbsp;</p>
<p>They need to recognize the fact that people have been traumatized by their experiences that were driven by the economic collapse. &nbsp;Even people who have mostly or basically recovered still feel like they are potentially on the edge of another economic collapse because they were traumatized - the rest are still catching up and many are looking at an economy that does not promise to make them feel secure at all - and that's not just about having a different lifestyle and regretting losing a better one - that's about feeling like having less makes them more vulnerable in the event that another blip or actual crash comes along. &nbsp;That's a big problem out there in my opinion.</p>
<p>Not much has been done to quell this Main Street set of fears, nor has enough been done to create hope that people might actually be able to relax a bit and feel like things are going to work out. &nbsp;Reporting stock market increases and better jobs reports that represent people earning lower wages doesn't cut it.</p>
<p>Anyway, they have to do more than just talk about Lily Ledbetter for women, or unions, minorities or farm workers, etc. &nbsp;They need to really talk about working people and what they deserve at all levels.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:37824">inclusiveheart</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55620834#c337">Mon Feb 09, 2015 at 11:14:11 AM PST</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  [ <a href="#c300">Parent</a> ] 
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
