<p>Because the mainstream media will NOT, I repeat, <strong>WILL NOT</strong>, separate the truth from established narrative. It will be both of them, presented as equally credible (realistically, both candidates lack credibility) yapping on the same issue. Hilary will talk about opportunity as a cure for inequality while serving Wall Street. The GOP candidate will go on about burdensome government as a cure for inequality while serving Wall Street. And the media isn't going to get into the muck in terms of whose "approach" is more likely to reduce income inequality, while, ahem, serving Wall Street.</p>
<p>And in this case, can you even blame the media for their false-balance, report what each side says, bullshit? When the Democrats are going out of their way to blur the lines themselves?</p>

