<li id="c43">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55613382">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">"Put-upon taxpayers"</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55613382#c43?mode=alone;showrate=1#c43">19+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:246193">Mr Robert</a>, <a href="/user/uid:254992">Jake Bodhi</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1179902">deadpan</a>, <a href="/user/uid:28799">k9disc</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100108">jello5929</a>, <a href="/user/uid:327009">goodpractice</a>, <a href="/user/uid:62088">the fan man</a>, <a href="/user/uid:947717">travelerxxx</a>, <a href="/user/uid:115624">Thomas Twinnings</a>, <a href="/user/uid:2823">Chi</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146659">notrouble</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1303">cslewis</a>, <a href="/user/uid:46465">NoMoreLies</a>, <a href="/user/uid:140186">arendt</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100167">Midwesterners</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75329">JVolvo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17036">Creosote</a>, <a href="/user/uid:125975">Metro99</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>&nbsp;Because Dems won't hammer hard on WAGES, and the pro-corporate destruction of them and unions over the last 30 years, then working-class types get opened up to GOP populism. For example, Scott Walker can seem populist by offering up property tax breaks as some kind of break for working people, and enough people are suckered in by it. This is even though the rich get most of the benefits of those tax breaks (because of higher property values) and despite the fact that wages and job growth have stagnated under Scotty.</p>
<p>&nbsp;When Dems don't respond by pointing to stagnating wages, unfair trade deals, and the utter failure of trickle-down economics in doing anything to help the average person over the last 30 years, then GOPs can get an advantage through "low-tax" talk- even as GOP policies keep people headed to the poor house.</p>
<p>&nbsp; I don't know why this doesn't sink in at the Beltway-based Dem offices, but it sure hasn't done so enough.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:347248">Jake formerly of the LP</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55613382#c43">Sun Feb 08, 2015 at 11:49:50 AM PST</a></p>
