<p>More like "someone". &nbsp;If you are casting Americans as victims of some impersonal forces you are missing the point. There are people who benefit from inequality, like employers who hire cheap labor. Or wealthy people (and corporations) who want to continue to benefit from low taxes (by historical and world standards) by cutting public services the less fortunate depend on.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:250087">Slightly Wobbly</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55613770#c71">Sun Feb 08, 2015 at 12:34:39 PM PST</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  [ <a href="#c5">Parent</a> ] 
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
  </div>
