<li id="c15">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55612769">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">It's all really just a version of </span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55612769#c15?mode=alone;showrate=1#c15">26+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:2823">Chi</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17553">Heart of the Rockies</a>, <a href="/user/uid:31900">pat bunny</a>, <a href="/user/uid:55657">Dem Beans</a>, <a href="/user/uid:62088">the fan man</a>, <a href="/user/uid:96369">Matt Z</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:139092">cybrestrike</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146420">maryabein</a>, <a href="/user/uid:171754">tapu dali</a>, <a href="/user/uid:198390">unapologeticliberal</a>, <a href="/user/uid:246193">Mr Robert</a>, <a href="/user/uid:259558">Free Jazz at High Noon</a>, <a href="/user/uid:307784">Portlaw</a>, <a href="/user/uid:327009">goodpractice</a>, <a href="/user/uid:347248">Jake formerly of the LP</a>, <a href="/user/uid:526036">starduster</a>, <a href="/user/uid:934178">Choco8</a>, <a href="/user/uid:989659">StevenWells</a>, <a href="/user/uid:1303">cslewis</a>, <a href="/user/uid:46465">NoMoreLies</a>, <a href="/user/uid:140186">arendt</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100167">Midwesterners</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75329">JVolvo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17036">Creosote</a>, <a href="/user/uid:125975">Metro99</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Government is Good vs Government is Bad.</p>
<p>Democrats have lost the war because they collectively retreated at each battle and bought into Republican framing every time.</p>
<p>With their reneging and retrenching and Austerity mongering and talk of entitlement reform and the like they vacated the battlefield. They NEVER speak about how government dollars are used for the benefit of private capital and how government subsidizes the profits of a few but socializes the losses among the many.</p>
<p>We are happy to bailout the large and the Too Big To Fail at the same time we will rip the food out of the hands of the hungry or the medicine away from the ill or the dollars out of the pockets of the poor. We will stand by and watch an entire generation become debt slaves for their education, with bizarre rules about if and when they can re-finance, etc.</p>
<p>We are one f-ked up country who allow all the wealth to be siphoned upward while our betters tell us that we can't afford public healthcare, or modern infrastructures, or high speed rail, or half way competent food safety oversight, or environmental protections, or financial regulation and oversight to protect us from predators.</p>
<p>We could afford all the things that would make a modern, enlightened comfortable country - healthcare, education, transportation, social safety nets, etc. but we CHOOSE to subsidize the wealthy and to wage wars and exploit labor.</p>
<p>Government is GREAT for the Masters of the Universe. The only part of government they want to drown is the little itty bitty portion that trickles down to actual citizens. That part is anathema to them because it is money that somehow didn't make it into their own pockets.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig">
“Human kindness has never weakened the stamina or softened the fiber of a free people. A nation does not have to be cruel to be tough.” FDR
</p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:308949">Phoebe Loosinhouse</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55612769#c15">Sun Feb 08, 2015 at 10:42:42 AM PST</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
  </div>
</li> 


	


