<p>The next-to-last paragraph of this diary says it all, and I've said it before: &nbsp;Like so many Dems who ran scared last year, she seems predisposed ot doing the same thing; that is, trying to run <em>not to lose,</em> rather than trying to run <em>to win.</em> &nbsp;Have they learned yet that this is <em>never</em> the way to win? &nbsp;Or are they going to repeat the same mistake of ignoring or avoiding any ideal of talking about what the Dems <em>have</em> accomplished, under Obama, and leave us with the bitter reality of 2017 and beyond?</p>
<p>Penn is gone (at least he'd <em>better</em> be, which is a good thing). &nbsp;She needs to dump Summers, STAT, and hire Reich <em>now.</em> &nbsp;Or it's going to look eerily similar to how the Yankees choked the 2004 AL Championship Series.</p>

