<p>It was Gore's election to lose, was my original point: he was always assumed as being the one to win, unless he screwed up. &nbsp;Which he did, in part by falling for Republican tactics (e.g., lie to place doubt on opponent's strongest qualities, lie and claim ownership of opponent's actual strengths, support a third party who further attacks your opponent) that I mentioned.</p>

