<li id="c45">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55613448">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">Clinton is offering Republican ideas about</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55613448#c45?mode=alone;showrate=1#c45">18+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:934178">Choco8</a>, <a href="/user/uid:246193">Mr Robert</a>, <a href="/user/uid:139092">cybrestrike</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100108">jello5929</a>, <a href="/user/uid:327009">goodpractice</a>, <a href="/user/uid:6493">dfarrah</a>, <a href="/user/uid:307784">Portlaw</a>, <a href="/user/uid:115624">Thomas Twinnings</a>, <a href="/user/uid:166438">gulfgal98</a>, <a href="/user/uid:2823">Chi</a>, <a href="/user/uid:55657">Dem Beans</a>, <a href="/user/uid:33131">LordMike</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146420">maryabein</a>, <a href="/user/uid:46465">NoMoreLies</a>, <a href="/user/uid:51000">schumann</a>, <a href="/user/uid:75329">JVolvo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:116838">elwior</a>, <a href="/user/uid:143254">BoiseBlue</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>economic populism. She's following a Republican vision.<br />
This.</p>
<blockquote>...<strong>inclusive capitalism,</strong> that contends that a majority of Americans do not want to punish the rich; they just want to feel that they, too, have a chance to succeed.</blockquote>
And this.
<blockquote>“The challenge, though, is to address inequality without embracing a politics of envy.”</blockquote>
This is looking at the problem through Republican eyes. She's placing the income inequality ball in the R's court.<br />
<em>Inclusive capitalism</em> is a poisonous concept. It's right up there with employers framed as <em>jobs providers</em>. It is this concept of labor as recipients of charity from their compassionate employers. The story is: employers don't actually <em>need</em> workers. They just want to be <strong>inclusive</strong>, and <strong>provide</strong> for the lowly classes.<br />
Clinton and her advisors see the Republican game as the only legitimate game. She can't be <em>outflanked on economic populism</em> because she's just flat out rejecting economic populism.

