<p>And I have no idea where you got this:</p>
<blockquote>Inclusive capitalism is a poisonous concept. It's right up there with employers framed as jobs providers. It is this concept of labor as recipients of charity from their compassionate employers. The story is: employers don't actually need workers. They just want to be inclusive, and provide for the lowly classes.<br />
&nbsp;Clinton and her advisors see the Republican game as the only legitimate game. She can't be outflanked on economic populism because she's just flat out rejecting economic populism.</blockquote>
Link?<br />

