<p>Problem is Hillary has a somewhat mixed record herself. I think if Hillary goes with a Warren or Dean type VP choice, and at least motivates lefft wing progressives to turn out, she still has a fair shot of winning on this issue. If she instead goes "centrist" there, while Jeb chooses a Huckabee or other right wing populist equivalent, yes she still has a decent chance to blow it.</p>
<p>Lets not forget it was largely Hillary's tin ear on these issues which caused her to squander a similarly sizable early lead against Obama in 2008.</p>

