<li id="c184">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55615457">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">If Climate Change</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55615457#c184?mode=alone;showrate=1#c184">2+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:31900">pat bunny</a>, <a href="/user/uid:100167">Midwesterners</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>is not addressed as the key issue and the Republicans win, every other issue will be moot and it won't matter who is in office, because it will be game over. Economic insecurity and stabilty rests on climate. If people can't make money because the snow is so high you can't get to work and the power lines are out for a few weeks, it doesn't matter if you make $200k or 20k. CLimate Change needs to be the Dems main push. Every other issue is rests on its back. Economy. Income inequality or just income itself, health care, food costs. The more drought, flood and violent storms, the more all of the above suffer. &nbsp;Climate Change needs to be the Dem's #1 calling card. .. the high paying home grown jobs will come with that path, and will solve many of the health issues, also.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:9053">yogipohaku</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55615457#c184">Sun Feb 08, 2015 at 04:26:15 PM PST</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
