<li id="c343">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55621776">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">they do not live in fear of being accused</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55621776#c343?mode=alone;showrate=1#c343">0+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>of class warfare. They live in fear of ACTUAL class warfare.</p>
<p>The third way isn't just some group of people who have decided they will try to split the difference (whatever the hell that means). They're people who pretty much ARE the 1%, they're just not nearly as Libertarian as the tea partiers.</p>
<p>The Clintons and Summers and their ilk certainly believe in a certain amount of taking care of those less off. But they absolutely do not want class warfare because they don't want to let that ball get rolling enough that they and their donors get hurt by it.</p>
<p>I don't say this to pile on Clinton - I'll vote for her in the general, and she's not really that different than Obama or Kerry on economic issues. But let's have a reality check that not being populist is by design, not out of fear that it won't play well.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig">
Want a progressive global warming novel, not a right wing rant? Go to www.edwardgtalbot.com and check out New World Orders
</p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:109546">eparrot</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55621776#c343">Mon Feb 09, 2015 at 01:01:41 PM PST</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
