<li id="c344">

  <div class="cx" id="cx55621843">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">You're still not a supporter, by inference.</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1363137/55621843#c344?mode=alone;showrate=1#c344">0+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>I won't seek to rehash our arguments of eight years ago Bob, but I'd put it a different way: She's struggling to formulate an economic message that allows her to stay true to her principles without alienating wealthy donors, particularly on Wall Street.</p>
<p>It's a quandary, no question about it. President Clinton's approach of tracking to the center had the benefit of giving the wealthy some reassurances that it wasn't against their interests to support him and Hillary tried to follow his example. The social/political dynamics don't lend themselves to this approach, anymore. Railing against affluenza motivates our base while alienating those who could compete with the recent Koch declaration.</p>
<p>I think she would do well to promote tax reform and I don't honestly see Republicans as having legs with the inequality approach. I just don't see how more tax cuts for the wealthy and less food for vulnerable children would make a difference.</p>
<p>Separately, I'm delighted by her choice of Podesta. He's a marked departure from Mark Penn (I don't usually care who is supporting her, but every time he opened his mouth, she fell three points in the polls) and I think he's a positive indication of change in her campaigning.</p>
<p>I expect that we'll have her announcement late this month or early next month and I hope that her campaign headquarters will be as convenient for me as her last one was.</p>
<p>I don't know that she could earn your support in any event Bob, but I'd like to see her try.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  
  <p class="sig">
The victorious strategist only seeks battle after the victory has been won, whereas he who is destined to defeat first fights and afterwards looks for victory.
</p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:66934">Pacifist</a> on <a href="/comments/1363137/55621843#c344">Mon Feb 09, 2015 at 01:10:13 PM PST</a></p>
